## Verification Checklist

After completing all phases:

```bash
# 1. Verify autoloads work
bundle exec ruby -e "require 'uniword'; puts Uniword::Wordprocessingml::Paragraph"
bundle exec ruby -e "require 'uniword'; puts Uniword::Drawingml::Theme"

# 2. Run full test suite
bundle exec rspec spec/

# 3. Run specific test categories
bundle exec rspec spec/uniword/wordprocessingml/
bundle exec rspec spec/uniword/drawingml/
bundle exec rspec spec/integration/

# 4. Check for any remaining issues
bundle exec rspec --format documentation spec/ 2>&1 | grep -i "failed\|error"
```

## Risk Assessment

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|------------|
| Breaking existing code | Add backwards compatibility aliases |
| Missing file references | Use grep to find all references before moving |
| Module nesting issues | Test autoload after each move |
| Test failures | Fix incrementally, commit after each fix |

## Rollback Plan

If issues arise:
1. Git provides full history - can revert individual commits
2. Work on feature branch to isolate changes
3. Tag current state before starting: `git tag pre-namespace-refactor`

